This spot on the map marks the location of the isle of Amia. On the souther tip the city of Cordor is marked and just to the west of that a small point that indicates the location of this light house.
The word 'Ruathym' is written over the depiction of this island. On the north east side there is a spot marking the location of Osthavn.
The name 'Caraigh' is written across the smaller isle south of the one marked Ruathym. There is a second, small island marked with the name 'Fortress Wiltun' to the north and east of Caraigh.
The name 'Brogendenstein' is written across the small island here.
The name 'Forrstakkr' is written over the small island drawn on the far northern edge of the map here.
The name 'Frozenfar' is written across the southern shore of the land at the far northern edge of the Sword Coast.

A decorative book sits on the small table, it is labeled "Visitor's Log". The book contains lines for names and comments made by the visitors. There are numerous names signed on the lines, but most are difficult to make out.
